# Design Document: Perfect World Neo Brutalism

## Overview

This design document describes the technical architecture for a complete MMORPG ecosystem website inspired by Perfect World, built with a Neo Brutalism Dark-Light visual identity. The system is a monorepo containing four applications (web, api, admin, launcher) and six shared packages, delivering a public-facing website, player dashboard, admin panel, and supporting backend microservices.

The architecture prioritizes:
- **Immersive visual experience** through 3D rendering (React Three Fiber), cinematic animations (Framer Motion + GSAP), and a strict Neo Brutalism design system
- **Realtime data flow** via Socket.IO websockets with graceful degradation to HTTP polling
- **Scalable microservices** using NestJS with PostgreSQL persistence, Redis caching, and Prisma ORM
- **Developer experience** through monorepo organization, shared packages, type safety, and automated CI/CD

### Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Frontend Framework | Next.js 16 (App Router) | SSR for SEO, RSC for performance, built-in routing |
| 3D Engine | React Three Fiber + Drei | Declarative 3D in React, ecosystem maturity |
| Animation | Framer Motion + GSAP | FM for layout/presence, GSAP for complex timelines |
| Backend | NestJS microservices | Module system, DI, WebSocket gateway, TypeScript native |
| Database | PostgreSQL + Prisma | Relational integrity, type-safe ORM, migrations |
| Cache | Redis | Rankings TTL, session store, pub/sub for realtime |
| Realtime | Socket.IO | Rooms/namespaces, auto-reconnect, fallback transport |
| Monorepo | Turborepo | Incremental builds, task caching, dependency graph |
| Deployment | Vercel (web) + Docker/VPS (api) | Edge CDN for frontend, container isolation for backend |

## Architecture

### High-Level System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Client["Client Layer"]
        WEB["apps/web<br/>Next.js 16"]
        ADMIN["apps/admin<br/>Next.js 16"]
        LAUNCHER["apps/launcher<br/>Electron/Tauri"]
    end

    subgraph Gateway["API Gateway Layer"]
        GW["API Gateway<br/>NestJS + Rate Limiter"]
    end

    subgraph Services["Microservices Layer"]
        AUTH["Auth Service"]
        PLAYER["Player Service"]
        GUILD["Guild Service"]
        RANK["Ranking Service"]
        MARKET["Marketplace Service"]
        NOTIF["Notification Service"]
        ANALYTICS["Analytics Service"]
        NEWS["News Service"]
    end

    subgraph Data["Data Layer"]
        PG["PostgreSQL"]
        REDIS["Redis"]
    end

    subgraph Realtime["Realtime Layer"]
        SIO["Socket.IO Server"]
    end

    WEB --> GW
    ADMIN --> GW
    LAUNCHER --> GW
    WEB --> SIO
    ADMIN --> SIO

    GW --> AUTH
    GW --> PLAYER
    GW --> GUILD
    GW --> RANK
    GW --> MARKET
    GW --> NOTIF
    GW --> ANALYTICS
    GW --> NEWS

    AUTH --> PG
    AUTH --> REDIS
    PLAYER --> PG
    GUILD --> PG
    RANK --> PG
    RANK --> REDIS
    MARKET --> PG
    MARKET --> REDIS
    NOTIF --> REDIS
    ANALYTICS --> PG
    NEWS --> PG

    SIO --> REDIS
    SIO --> NOTIF
```

### Monorepo Structure

```
perfect-world/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/                    # Public website + Player Dashboard (Next.js 16)
│   ├── api/                    # Backend microservices (NestJS)
│   ├── admin/                  # Admin Panel (Next.js 16)
│   └── launcher/               # Desktop launcher (Electron/Tauri)
├── packages/
│   ├── ui/                     # Shared UI components (Neo Brutalism design system)
│   ├── auth/                   # Authentication utilities (JWT, OAuth helpers)
│   ├── configs/                # Shared configurations (ESLint, TypeScript, Tailwind)
│   ├── sdk/                    # API client SDK (typed fetch wrappers)
│   ├── database/               # Prisma schema, migrations, seed scripts
│   └── shared/                 # Common types, constants, validation schemas
├── docker-compose.yml          # Local dev environment (PG, Redis)
├── turbo.json                  # Turborepo pipeline configuration
├── package.json                # Root workspace configuration
└── .github/workflows/          # CI/CD pipelines
```

### Request Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client (Browser)
    participant N as Next.js (SSR/RSC)
    participant G as API Gateway
    participant S as Service
    participant D as PostgreSQL
    participant R as Redis
    participant WS as Socket.IO

    C->>N: Page Request
    N->>G: Server-side data fetch
    G->>G: Rate limit check
    G->>G: JWT validation
    G->>S: Route to service
    S->>R: Check cache
    alt Cache hit
        R-->>S: Cached data
    else Cache miss
        S->>D: Query database
        D-->>S: Result
        S->>R: Update cache
    end
    S-->>G: Response
    G-->>N: JSON data
    N-->>C: Rendered HTML + hydration

    Note over C,WS: Realtime updates
    C->>WS: Connect (JWT auth)
    WS->>R: Subscribe to channels
    R-->>WS: Pub/Sub event
    WS-->>C: Push update
```

